<paragraph blockId="7.[189,334,1456,1482]" box="[189,334,1456,1482]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,334,1456,1482]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,334,1456,1482]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,1398,1502,1564]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
MEASUREMENTS. Body length including forewing: male 4.0– 
<quantity box="[912,1005,1502,1529]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.3" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="4.3">4.3 mm</quantity>
(N = 3); forewing length: male 
<quantity box="[189,330,1537,1564]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.65" metricValueMax="3.7" metricValueMin="3.6" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="3.65" valueMax="3.7" valueMin="3.6">3.6–3.7 mm</quantity>
(N = 3).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,1399,1603,1946]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
COLORATION. General coloration dark yellowish brown (
<figureCitation box="[836,903,1603,1629]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1966,1992]" captionTargetBox="[228,1361,823,1910]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[206,1382,812,1929]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. Neobelocera russa sp. nov., holotype (GUGC-FS-TN-20100801). A. Male habitus, dorsal view. B. Same, lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Same, lateral view. E. Face. F. Forewing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3817125" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3817125/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
A–F). Vertex, pronotum, mesonotum dirty yellowish brown, except Y-shaped carina of vertex, all carinae of pronotum and mesonotum yellowish white (
<figureCitation box="[272,367,1673,1700]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1966,1992]" captionTargetBox="[228,1361,823,1910]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[206,1382,812,1929]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. Neobelocera russa sp. nov., holotype (GUGC-FS-TN-20100801). A. Male habitus, dorsal view. B. Same, lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Same, lateral view. E. Face. F. Forewing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3817125" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3817125/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
). Frons and genae brown, except broad transversal stripe below level of lower margin of eyes and narrow stripe of apex yellowish white, along near apex of median carina of frons and inner margin of lateral carinae of genae with several short transversal stripes, yellowish white. Clypeus yellowish brown to brown (
<figureCitation box="[533,629,1779,1805]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1966,1992]" captionTargetBox="[228,1361,823,1910]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[206,1382,812,1929]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. Neobelocera russa sp. nov., holotype (GUGC-FS-TN-20100801). A. Male habitus, dorsal view. B. Same, lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Same, lateral view. E. Face. F. Forewing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3817125" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3817125/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
). Eyes dirty yellowish brown. Ocelli reddish brown. Antennae brown, except lateral margins of first segment yellowish white (
<figureCitation box="[957,1051,1814,1840]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1966,1992]" captionTargetBox="[228,1361,823,1910]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[206,1382,812,1929]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. Neobelocera russa sp. nov., holotype (GUGC-FS-TN-20100801). A. Male habitus, dorsal view. B. Same, lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Same, lateral view. E. Face. F. Forewing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3817125" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3817125/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
). Legs yellowish white, with dark brown maculations. Forewing light yellowish white, almost hyaline, basal part near costal margin with big infuscate markings, and apical part from transverse veins to apex with dark brown markings, veins with white spots (
<figureCitation box="[467,556,1920,1946]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1966,1992]" captionTargetBox="[228,1361,823,1910]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[206,1382,812,1929]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. Neobelocera russa sp. nov., holotype (GUGC-FS-TN-20100801). A. Male habitus, dorsal view. B. Same, lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Same, lateral view. E. Face. F. Forewing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3817125" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3817125/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 3F</figureCitation>
). Wings hyaline with veins dark brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,1399,267,505]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
HEAD AND THORAX. Head including eyes almost as wide as pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[1032,1129,267,293]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1895,1921]" captionTargetBox="[201,1387,778,1840]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1398,770,1850]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Neobelocera russa sp. nov., holotype (GUGC-FS-TN-20100801). A. Head and thorax, dorsal view. B. Face. C. Forewing. D. Male genitalia, posterior view. E. Same, lateral view. F. Aedeagus, posterior view. G. Same, lateral view. H. Genital style, posterior view. I. Same, lateral view. Scale bars: A–B, D–I = 0.2 mm; C = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3817127" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3817127/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
). Vertex wider at base than long medially about 2.57: 1 (
<figureCitation box="[592,688,302,329]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1895,1921]" captionTargetBox="[201,1387,778,1840]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1398,770,1850]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Neobelocera russa sp. nov., holotype (GUGC-FS-TN-20100801). A. Head and thorax, dorsal view. B. Face. C. Forewing. D. Male genitalia, posterior view. E. Same, lateral view. F. Aedeagus, posterior view. G. Same, lateral view. H. Genital style, posterior view. I. Same, lateral view. Scale bars: A–B, D–I = 0.2 mm; C = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3817127" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3817127/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
). Frons in middle line longer than wide at widest part about 1.74: 1, widest above level of lower margin of eyes. Postclypeus at base almost as wide as frons at apex (
<figureCitation box="[198,294,373,399]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1895,1921]" captionTargetBox="[201,1387,778,1840]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1398,770,1850]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Neobelocera russa sp. nov., holotype (GUGC-FS-TN-20100801). A. Head and thorax, dorsal view. B. Face. C. Forewing. D. Male genitalia, posterior view. E. Same, lateral view. F. Aedeagus, posterior view. G. Same, lateral view. H. Genital style, posterior view. I. Same, lateral view. Scale bars: A–B, D–I = 0.2 mm; C = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3817127" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3817127/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
). Antennae with first segment shorter than second segment about 0.65: 1, second segment cylindrical, longer than wide about 2.80: 1 (
<figureCitation box="[694,785,408,434]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1895,1921]" captionTargetBox="[201,1387,778,1840]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1398,770,1850]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Neobelocera russa sp. nov., holotype (GUGC-FS-TN-20100801). A. Head and thorax, dorsal view. B. Face. C. Forewing. D. Male genitalia, posterior view. E. Same, lateral view. F. Aedeagus, posterior view. G. Same, lateral view. H. Genital style, posterior view. I. Same, lateral view. Scale bars: A–B, D–I = 0.2 mm; C = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3817127" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3817127/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
). Pronotum subequal to vertex medially. Mesonotum longer than vertex and pronotum combined about 2.25: 1 (
<figureCitation box="[866,960,443,469]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1895,1921]" captionTargetBox="[201,1387,778,1840]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1398,770,1850]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Neobelocera russa sp. nov., holotype (GUGC-FS-TN-20100801). A. Head and thorax, dorsal view. B. Face. C. Forewing. D. Male genitalia, posterior view. E. Same, lateral view. F. Aedeagus, posterior view. G. Same, lateral view. H. Genital style, posterior view. I. Same, lateral view. Scale bars: A–B, D–I = 0.2 mm; C = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3817127" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3817127/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
). Forewing longer in middle line than wide at widest part about 3.25: 1 (
<figureCitation box="[589,682,478,505]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1895,1921]" captionTargetBox="[201,1387,778,1840]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1398,770,1850]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Neobelocera russa sp. nov., holotype (GUGC-FS-TN-20100801). A. Head and thorax, dorsal view. B. Face. C. Forewing. D. Male genitalia, posterior view. E. Same, lateral view. F. Aedeagus, posterior view. G. Same, lateral view. H. Genital style, posterior view. I. Same, lateral view. Scale bars: A–B, D–I = 0.2 mm; C = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3817127" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3817127/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,1399,544,746]" lastBlockId="9.[189,1399,267,364]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
MALE GENITALIA. Anal segment small, ring-like (
<figureCitation box="[777,877,544,570]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1895,1921]" captionTargetBox="[201,1387,778,1840]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1398,770,1850]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Neobelocera russa sp. nov., holotype (GUGC-FS-TN-20100801). A. Head and thorax, dorsal view. B. Face. C. Forewing. D. Male genitalia, posterior view. E. Same, lateral view. F. Aedeagus, posterior view. G. Same, lateral view. H. Genital style, posterior view. I. Same, lateral view. Scale bars: A–B, D–I = 0.2 mm; C = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3817127" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3817127/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
). Pygofer in profile much longer ventrally than dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[364,459,579,605]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1895,1921]" captionTargetBox="[201,1387,778,1840]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1398,770,1850]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Neobelocera russa sp. nov., holotype (GUGC-FS-TN-20100801). A. Head and thorax, dorsal view. B. Face. C. Forewing. D. Male genitalia, posterior view. E. Same, lateral view. F. Aedeagus, posterior view. G. Same, lateral view. H. Genital style, posterior view. I. Same, lateral view. Scale bars: A–B, D–I = 0.2 mm; C = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3817127" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3817127/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
), in posterior view with opening longer than wide, ventral margin with three medioventral processes, median one longer than lateral ones, truncate apically, lateral ones stout, tapering (
<figureCitation box="[306,407,649,676]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1895,1921]" captionTargetBox="[201,1387,778,1840]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1398,770,1850]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Neobelocera russa sp. nov., holotype (GUGC-FS-TN-20100801). A. Head and thorax, dorsal view. B. Face. C. Forewing. D. Male genitalia, posterior view. E. Same, lateral view. F. Aedeagus, posterior view. G. Same, lateral view. H. Genital style, posterior view. I. Same, lateral view. Scale bars: A–B, D–I = 0.2 mm; C = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3817127" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3817127/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[568,642,649,676]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1895,1921]" captionTargetBox="[201,1387,778,1840]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1398,770,1850]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Neobelocera russa sp. nov., holotype (GUGC-FS-TN-20100801). A. Head and thorax, dorsal view. B. Face. C. Forewing. D. Male genitalia, posterior view. E. Same, lateral view. F. Aedeagus, posterior view. G. Same, lateral view. H. Genital style, posterior view. I. Same, lateral view. Scale bars: A–B, D–I = 0.2 mm; C = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3817127" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3817127/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
F–G) with phallobase, phallus tubular, bent ventrad medially, with node at apex, middle dorsal with a spinous process, directed dorsad, apex with 2 long spinous processes. In addition, 2 processes at subapical part of phallus, right one strongly curved. Phallobase slender, tubular, arising from base of aedeagus, running dorsad, then curving caudad, after median part, turned left then ventrad, tapering apically. Genital styles simple, long, reaching to ventral margin of anal segment, swollen subapically (
<figureCitation box="[550,645,338,364]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1895,1921]" captionTargetBox="[201,1387,778,1840]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1398,770,1850]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Neobelocera russa sp. nov., holotype (GUGC-FS-TN-20100801). A. Head and thorax, dorsal view. B. Face. C. Forewing. D. Male genitalia, posterior view. E. Same, lateral view. F. Aedeagus, posterior view. G. Same, lateral view. H. Genital style, posterior view. I. Same, lateral view. Scale bars: A–B, D–I = 0.2 mm; C = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3817127" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3817127/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 4H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
