<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,303,267,293]" box="[189,303,267,293]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,267,293]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,267,293]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1399,313,798]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
This new species is assigned to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ding &amp; Yang" authorityYear="1986" box="[689,839,313,339]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Neobelocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[689,839,313,339]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Neobelocera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because the antennal segment I is subsagittate, markedly flattened, with a median longitudinal carina, the ventral apical angle longer than dorsal apical angle (
<figureCitation box="[272,369,384,410]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1895,1921]" captionTargetBox="[201,1387,778,1840]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1398,770,1850]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Neobelocera russa sp. nov., holotype (GUGC-FS-TN-20100801). A. Head and thorax, dorsal view. B. Face. C. Forewing. D. Male genitalia, posterior view. E. Same, lateral view. F. Aedeagus, posterior view. G. Same, lateral view. H. Genital style, posterior view. I. Same, lateral view. Scale bars: A–B, D–I = 0.2 mm; C = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3817127" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3817127/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
). This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Chen, 2003" authorityName="Chen" authorityYear="2003" box="[710,1046,384,410]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Neobelocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lanpingensis">
<emphasis box="[710,896,384,410]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">N. lanpingensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Chen X. S." box="[907,1046,384,410]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="1 - 4" refId="ref6123" refString="Chen X. S. 2003. A new species of the genus Neobelocera (Homoptera: Delphacidae) from China. Zootaxa 290: 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="2003">
Chen, 
<quantity box="[987,1046,384,410]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.087619999999999" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="in" value="2003.0">2003</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in having the body elongate (
<figureCitation box="[198,265,419,445]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1966,1992]" captionTargetBox="[228,1361,823,1910]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[206,1382,812,1929]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. Neobelocera russa sp. nov., holotype (GUGC-FS-TN-20100801). A. Male habitus, dorsal view. B. Same, lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Same, lateral view. E. Face. F. Forewing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3817125" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3817125/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
A–B), forewings long and narrow, apex oblique and tapering, with blackish brown markings, and with white spots or white short stripes at intervals (
<figureCitation box="[783,871,454,480]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1966,1992]" captionTargetBox="[228,1361,823,1910]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[206,1382,812,1929]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. Neobelocera russa sp. nov., holotype (GUGC-FS-TN-20100801). A. Male habitus, dorsal view. B. Same, lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Same, lateral view. E. Face. F. Forewing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3817125" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3817125/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 3F</figureCitation>
), frons with pale transverse band below level of lower margin of eyes (
<figureCitation box="[495,586,489,516]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1966,1992]" captionTargetBox="[228,1361,823,1910]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[206,1382,812,1929]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. Neobelocera russa sp. nov., holotype (GUGC-FS-TN-20100801). A. Male habitus, dorsal view. B. Same, lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Same, lateral view. E. Face. F. Forewing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3817125" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3817125/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
), male pygofer with medioventral processes (
<figureCitation box="[1133,1229,489,516]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1895,1921]" captionTargetBox="[201,1387,778,1840]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1398,770,1850]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Neobelocera russa sp. nov., holotype (GUGC-FS-TN-20100801). A. Head and thorax, dorsal view. B. Face. C. Forewing. D. Male genitalia, posterior view. E. Same, lateral view. F. Aedeagus, posterior view. G. Same, lateral view. H. Genital style, posterior view. I. Same, lateral view. Scale bars: A–B, D–I = 0.2 mm; C = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3817127" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3817127/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
), phallus with four spinous processes at apex and near apex, phallobase slender and long (
<figureCitation box="[1069,1138,524,551]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1895,1921]" captionTargetBox="[201,1387,778,1840]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1398,770,1850]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Neobelocera russa sp. nov., holotype (GUGC-FS-TN-20100801). A. Head and thorax, dorsal view. B. Face. C. Forewing. D. Male genitalia, posterior view. E. Same, lateral view. F. Aedeagus, posterior view. G. Same, lateral view. H. Genital style, posterior view. I. Same, lateral view. Scale bars: A–B, D–I = 0.2 mm; C = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3817127" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3817127/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
F–G). However, it can be distinguished from the latter by the following features: (1) frons (
<figureCitation box="[985,1073,560,586]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1966,1992]" captionTargetBox="[228,1361,823,1910]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[206,1382,812,1929]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. Neobelocera russa sp. nov., holotype (GUGC-FS-TN-20100801). A. Male habitus, dorsal view. B. Same, lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Same, lateral view. E. Face. F. Forewing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3817125" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3817125/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
) along near apex of median carina with several short transversal stripes, yellowish white (in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chen" authorityYear="2003" box="[929,1110,595,621]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Neobelocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lanpingensis">
<emphasis box="[929,1110,595,621]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">N. lanpingensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, frons without yellowish white transverse stripes subapically); (2) genae (
